==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|scieran|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|skeran|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|(s)ker-|lang=en}}.  Cognate with Dutch {{term|scheren|lang=nl}}, German {{term|scheren|lang=de}}, Norwegian {{term|skjære|lang=no}}, Swedish {{term|skära|lang=sv}}; and (''from Indo-European'') with Ancient Greek {{term|κείρω||I cut off|tr=keirō|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, Latin {{term|caro||flesh|lang=la}}, Lithuanian {{term|skìrti||separate|lang=lt}}, Welsh {{term|ysgar||separate|lang=cy}}.

